The 27 of the 29 students of the College of Forestry Mechanisation Afaka in Kaduna kidnapped in March, have been released by their abductors. According to a credible source, one of the intermediaries who collected the freed students at a designated point, confirmed the development. Recall that parents of the students had on Tuesday stormed the National Assembly in Abuja to protest the continued abduction of their children and government’s apparent indifference. Details later…